      <div class="msgContentFrame">I felt your pain all the way to level 30 GLA. <br />I have been digging into forums since I started grinding in parties trying to find the best SP advice. <br />I kept trying to refine my actions to maximize SP gains with VERY little luck. <br />When I was 30 I grouped with 14 people and fought something much higher then I was. <br />Since I was the lowest and the tank I had terrible aggro. <br />So I started Taunting/Provoking on cooldowns and BOOM!!! <br />My SP shot through the roof 400 to 500 per kill. <br />I thought this has to be because of the level of creature or the size of our party. <br />So I have been trying the taunt/provoke on cooldown for a few days now in groups and the result is the same. It even worked in a group with 5 tanks fighting for aggro.  <br /> <br />I was VERY excited to hit surplus for my first time. <br />The feeling dwindled very quickly though.  <br /> <br />P.S. I do not use my shield and I realized I will have to play catch up.  <br /> <br />The way I grind is NOT the way I would fight a NM, quest, or in a Raid situation. <br />The more damage I take the more healers can heal, and the more SP they gain. <br /> <br /> <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1819554.png" height="144" width="482" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
