      <div class="msgContentFrame">Yesterday when soloing &quot;green&quot; difficulty mob, I tried 2 way for getting more Sword SP... <br /> <br />First one, was using only my Sword without guarding my self. <br />Second one, was playing normaly has a tank with Sword, Shield and Phalanx. <br /> <br />With the sword only I was getting 20-150 Sword SP. <br />With the Sword, shield and Phalanx i was getting 100-200+ Sword SP and Shield like 0-50. <br /> <br />I understand that my tried is not in a 500 SP party and only soloing, but this is what i think about my soloing test : <br /> <br />When using Sword only, I was gaining from my sword and some Parying. With my Sword-Shield, I was gaining a lot from Phalanx. With normal hit-parying I was getting like 10-20 SP each, but with Phalanx i was getting 40-50 SP. So, it seems that i was getting more in the Sword-Shield test because Phalanx give more when you get SP from it. After that, I realize that the Shield SP was really low compare to when i Duo with my friend CON23. The thing is that the Shield is slow to lvl up, then it seems that when you skill on a higher mob, you gain Shield SP really faster.  <br /> <br />After all the testing, I think that our problem is that because our shield is really low (I'm 20GLD and 10 Shield, and I'm using shield for 90% of the time) shield will gain a lot until its the same lvl has our job... If I'm right about that, then the only way for gaining more is to wait that SE made some rectification about that. But my testing was for Soloing and I can't get the 500 cap will soloing, so maybe you can get 500SP in Party when not using your Shield, that's something that needed to be test ^^<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/965232.png" height="144" width="482" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
