      <div class="msgContentFrame">I agree with magic cat so much that i had to sign up and post ^^ <br /> <br />If you're not using your shield you are really screwing yourself...  <br /> <br />First off, you don't always get shield points for blocking. I'd say 1/10 times or so, even with a freshly repaired shield, I get swordskill instead. On top of that, you'll usually get at least two blocks per guard, which can equal up to two landed phalanx strikes.  <br /> <br />Phalanx is amazing because it has a virtually free stamina cost. Sometimes I can even land three phalanxes off of one guard (that is, three blocks and three sword attacks for very little stamina) the only catch is you have to keep your TP up. (Generally 2 light slashes and two blocks = enough tp for 3 phalanxes) <br /> <br />If you're maxing your SP very early you might want to try moving to a group of monsters that you can cut through a bit quicker to increase the pace of gain. If it takes you ten minutes to kill one mob and get 300sw/200sh, you might want to go to somewhere you can kill 5 in ten minutes and get closer to or over 1k total points in 10min. <br /> <br />Right now, as a Rnk 26 GLA with Shield @ 16 my group can tear through crabs in Cass. Hollow without stopping, and I usually get at least 200/100 sword/shield or vice versa. One thing you shouldn't be worried about is your shieldkill gain messing with your swordskill gain. <br /> <br />Also if you have plenty of tp for future phalanxes then use provoke and taunt. This gives you SP and lets the damage dealers get theirs by doing what they do best. Be a team player ; ] <br /> <br /></div>
